summary: This document contains a summary of account balances and transaction details for a checking account held at Deutsche Bank Trust Company Americas. It outlines various debits and credits over the month of September 2014, including preauthorized debits and checks paid. The document is part of a financial record related to the Epstein case.
keyFacts: The document details account transactions from September 1, 2014, to September 30, 2014.
The account had a beginning balance of $110,718.81 and an ending balance of $48,530.55.
Multiple preauthorized debits were made, including payments to ADP for tax and payroll services.
There were checks paid during the month, including check number 1029 for $3,752.55.
The document is marked as confidential and is part of a larger set of financial records related to the Epstein investigation.
